Isaiah 14-22 <pb/>“I will rise up against them,” declares the LORD of hosts, “and will cut off from Babylon name and <f>ⓑ</f>remnant, <f>ⓒ</f>descendants and posterity,” declares the LORD.
Isaiah 14-23 “And I will make it a possession of the <f>ⓓ</f>hedgehog, <f>[5]</f> and pools of water, and I will sweep it with the broom of destruction,” declares the LORD of hosts.
